('062265', 'ENGR', 'EGR', 'ENGR', '260', 'Nanoscale Science and Technology', '.Overview of key elements of physics, chemistry, biology and engineering underlying this interdisciplinary field. Bulk vs surface properties of materials. Surface phenomena and quantum phenomena. Self-assembly and soft lithography. Nanoscale materials characterization. Carbon nanotubes, inorganic molecules for electronics, biological and bio-inspired materials. Emerging applications of nanoscale materials. Prerequisite: Graduate standing. ( 2 units)', '2.00', '2.00', 'A'),
