('062307', 'UGRD', 'AS', 'THTR', '41', 'Theatre History I', 'First in a three-course sequence exploring the development of Western theatre as an art form and a complex social institution. Theatre History I begins in pre-history, considering various theories that try to account for the origin of theatre, and continues with a study of the texts and performance practices of ancient Greece, Republican and Imperial Rome, and Medieval Europe.', '4.00', '4.00', 'A'),
