('062339', 'ENGR', 'EGR', 'ENGR', '304', 'Building Global Teams', 'Challenges of working virtually and globally. Building global teams. Working across cultures - diverse approaches to managing task, time and hierarchy. Social interactions and decision making. Culture&apos;s impact on teamwork. Global leader dimensions. Trust building. Working across cultures and distance. Achieving goals while managing differences. Empowering self and others. Business practices in China, India, Russia, and other countries.', '2.00', '2.00', 'A'),
('062363', 'ENGR', 'EGR', 'ELEN', '391', 'Process & Device Simulation with TCAD', 'The course involves  TCAD tools and methods as a design aid. Utilization of TCAD will enable visualization of the physical device quantities at different stages of the design. It will also help students understanding  the influence of process parameters on the device and circuit performance. Individuals who take the course are expected to become an expert in the field of TCAD modeling and should be able to use their experiences in industry and development fields. 2 units.', '2.00', '2.00', 'A'),
('062364', 'ENGR', 'EGR', 'ELEN', '226', 'DSP Design in FPGA', 'Introduction to current state of the art design and implementation of FPGA signbal processing systems with emphasis on digital communications applications.   Prerequisites:  ELEN 133 or 234, and ELEN 127 or the equivalent.', '2.00', '2.00', 'A'),
('062366', 'ENGR', 'EGR', 'EMGT', '285', 'Relationship Management', 'Skills taught for characterizing, developing, and leveraging, various key relationships in one&apos;s organization. Articulating	and developing interaction models, dependency analyses, and team structures.  Developing tools to manage\noutsourcing models, partnerships,	co-development strategies and organizational synergy in line with overall business objectives. (2 units).', '2.00', '2.00', 'A'),
